If you click on the &#39;**Last Modified Date**&#39; column header, it will sort the items by the dates displayed. Clicking the same column header again will toggle the sort from Ascending to Descending and vice versa.

    $path = &#39;C:\Test&#39;

    # get an array of subfolder objects in the root folder $path
    $folders = Get-ChildItem -Path $path -Directory  # should we add -Recurse to also dig into any subfolder?

