Today I realized my sticky footer starts to flicker in Mobile Safari on iOS.

Here&#39;s what happens:

 1. You scroll down the page in Portrait mode.
 2. The address bar on top shrinks and the bottom bar is moved out of the screen.
 3. As soon as both disappear completely the sticky footer jumps up for a second and then is position on the bottom again, as expected.

A few observations:

 - This only happens when scrolling fast and only when the iOS bars are visible at first and shrink while scrolling.
 - You have to scroll fast to make this happen.
 - The jump / flickering does not appear while the bars are animated but when the animation is complete.

